\pi \cot(\pi x)
\pi \cot(\pi x)=\sum_{k \to \infty}^{\infty} \frac{1}{x+k}=\frac{1}{x}+\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}\left(\frac{1}{x+n}+\frac{1}{x-n} \right) \text{ for } x\in \mathbb{R} \backslash \mathbb{Z}.
\int \pi \cot(\pi x) = \log\left(\sin(\pi x) \right)+C.
\displaystyle \zeta (2)=\frac{\pi^2}{6}
\displaystyle \zeta (2)=\frac{\pi^2}{6}
